  "summary": "## Summary: AI-Powered Smart Label Engine\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**Database Layer**\n- Added `smart_labels` table: stores user-defined labels with name, natural-language prompt, color, and active status; RLS policies with `crudPolicy` for tenant isolation\n- Added `smart_label_items` junction table: polymorphic label-to-item associations supporting email, card, action_item, and meeting types; tracks confidence scores and assignment source (ai/manual); RLS policies via subquery through parent `smart_labels`\n- Created SQL migration with proper indexes, unique constraints, and RLS policy setup\n\n**AI Classification Pipeline**\n- Added `PROMPT_SMART_LABEL_CLASSIFY` to the AI prompts registry with a default prompt that evaluates items against user-defined label rules and returns confidence-scored matches\n- Built classification engine (`lib/smartLabels/classify.ts`) that:\n  - Fetches item content from the database based on type (email, card, action_item, meeting)\n  - Passes content + all active label prompts to the AI model\n  - Parses structured JSON responses with confidence scores\n  - Only applies labels with confidence >= 70 (conservative matching)\n  - Supports idempotent single-item and batch classification\n  - Truncates content to 3000 chars and limits to 20 labels per pass for cost control\n\n**Library Layer**\n- Built `lib/smartLabels/labels.ts` with full CRUD operations: create, read, update, delete labels; assign/remove labels from items; batch-fetch labels for multiple items; check classification status\n- Built `lib/smartLabels/db.ts` following the existing neon tagged template pattern\n\n**API Routes**\n- `GET /api/smart-labels` — List all smart labels for the authenticated user\n- `POST /api/smart-labels` — Create a new smart label with Zod validation\n- `GET /api/smart-labels/:id` — Get a single smart label\n- `PATCH /api/smart-labels/:id` — Update label name, prompt, color, or active status\n- `DELETE /api/smart-labels/:id` — Delete label with cascading item removal\n- `POST /api/smart-labels/classify` — Single item or batch classification against all active labels\n- `GET /api/smart-labels/:id/items` — Get all items tagged with a label\n- `POST /api/smart-labels/:id/items` — Manually assign label to an item\n- `DELETE /api/smart-labels/:id/items` — Remove label from an item\n- `POST /api/smart-labels/items` — Batch-fetch smart labels for a list of items (for inbox rendering)\n\n**Validation**\n- Added Zod schemas: `createSmartLabelSchema`, `updateSmartLabelSchema`, `classifySmartLabelsSchema`, `batchClassifySmartLabelsSchema`\n\n**Admin UI**\n- Built `SmartLabelsClient.tsx` — Full label management page with:\n  - Expandable label cards showing name, prompt, color, and active status\n  - Inline editing with name, prompt textarea, and 8-color preset picker\n  - Create label form with validation\n  - Pause/activate toggle\n  - Delete with confirmation\n  - Batch AI classification trigger with item type selector (emails, cards, action items)\n  - Loading skeleton and empty state\n  - Proper toast notifications using the existing Toast component\n\n**Navigation**\n- Added \"Smart Labels\" entry to the SideNav with a sparkle icon between \"AI Prompts\" and \"Extensions\"\n- Added `isActive` route matching for `/admin/smart-labels`\n\n**Inbox Integration**\n- Added `SmartLabelChips` component displaying color-coded label chips with confidence tooltips\n- Integrated smart label batch-fetching when inbox emails load (via `useEffect`)\n- Rendered smart label chips alongside existing email label chips in each email row\n- Added smart label filter pills to the inbox filter bar (separated by `|` divider from existing labels)\n- Client-side filtering by smart label works alongside existing label filtering\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/db/schema.ts` — Added `smartLabels` and `smartLabelItems` table definitions with RLS\n- `lib/ai/prompts.ts` — Added `PROMPT_SMART_LABEL_CLASSIFY` constant and default prompt\n- `lib/validators/schemas.ts` — Added smart label validation schemas\n- `components/ui/SideNav.tsx` — Added SmartLabelsIcon and nav entry\n- `app/(app)/inbox/page.tsx` — Added smart label state, fetching, chips component, and filtering\n- `drizzle/migrations/meta/_journal.json` — Added migration entry\n\n### Files Created\n- `drizzle/migrations/0032_smart-labels.sql` — Database migration with tables, indexes, and RLS policies\n- `types/smartLabel.ts` — TypeScript interfaces for SmartLabel, SmartLabelItem, SmartLabelChip\n- `lib/smartLabels/db.ts` — Neon database connection module\n- `lib/smartLabels/labels.ts` — CRUD and query functions for smart labels\n- `lib/smartLabels/classify.ts` — AI classification engine with content fetching and batch processing\n- `app/api/smart-labels/route.ts` — List and create labels\n- `app/api/smart-labels/[id]/route.ts` — Get, update, delete individual labels\n- `app/api/smart-labels/classify/route.ts` — Classification trigger endpoint\n- `app/api/smart-labels/[id]/items/route.ts` — Label-to-item assignment management\n- `app/api/smart-labels/items/route.ts` — Batch label lookup for rendering\n- `app/(app)/admin/smart-labels/page.tsx` — Server component page\n- `app/(app)/admin/smart-labels/SmartLabelsClient.tsx` — Client component with full management UI\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Run the migration `0032_smart-labels.sql` against the Neon database before using\n- The AI classification uses the OpenRouter default model; can be customized via the AI Prompts admin page under \"Smart Label Classification\"\n- Classification is currently triggered manually from the admin UI; can be integrated into email/card ingestion webhooks by calling `classifyItem()` after item creation\n- The `item_id` column stores all IDs as strings (emails are `number.toString()`, cards/meetings are UUIDs) for polymorphic flexibility\n- Smart labels are per-tenant and isolated by RLS policies\n- The batch classification limit is 20 items per pass and 20 labels per classification call to control AI costs"
}